author: Inside Edition
description: Police say a car with a young couple was going 95 miles an hour before it crashed. Daniel Waterman took the brunt of the crash sitting in the passenger seat. Police thought it was an accident, but investigators say when Waterman woke up from the coma, he told them it was not an accident. He said his girlfriend, Leigha Mumby, tried to kill him. Waterman died after eight months of battling to stay alive. Mumby was arrested. She has pleaded not guilty to vehicular manslaughter.
title: Man Wakes From Coma And Says Girlfriend Tried To Kill Him: Cops

author: Inside Edition
description: Karen Read is accused of running over her Boston police officer boyfriend with her car and leaving him to die. The first trial ended in a hung jury. Read's lawyers claim she was set up. During the first trial, there was a stunning show of support for Read.
title: The Karen Read Retrial - The Verdict

author: Inside Edition
description: Kristi Hemric and her husband David's home in Manhattan is beginning to look a lot like Christmas. Is it too soon? It's the big debate from coast to coast: decorate for Christmas right after Halloween, or follow tradition and at least wait until after Thanksgiving? Polls say that 42% of Americans say it is too early to decorate for Christmas, but 46% say it's about the right time. Streams for holiday classic "All I Want For Christmas Is You," by the queen of Christmas herself, Mariah Carey, are up 500%.
title: Is It Too Early To Deck The Halls?

author: Inside Edition
description: As SNAP benefits are imperiled and frozen due to the government shutdown, many people are struggling to buy food – and wondering how they will feed their families in the weeks ahead. Food pantries are doing a brisk business. But people are finding and creating new ways to help their neighbors – like acting as a so-called "Grocery Buddy." JoWanda Ward told Inside Edition Digital, "It's just a program to help people get food and survive the month."
title: How 'Grocery Buddies' Are Stepping In To Help Feed Their Neighbors

author: Inside Edition
description: The most famous red carpet gown is back. Supermodel Amber Valletta wore the iconic Versace jungle-print dress, made famous by Jennifer Lopez 25 years ago. The jaw-dropping gown was worn by Lopez at the Grammys in 2000. But it was Valletta who wore it first, on the Versace runway in 1999. She looked just as stunning Sunday at the fashion awards event in New York City, where she honored the dress' designer, Donatella Versace.
title: Versace's Iconic Jungle-Print Dress Returns

author: Inside Edition
description: Golfer Paige Spiranac posted an emotional video speaking candidly about the impact of cruel online trolling. The most recent barrage of attacks came after Spiranac appeared at the Internet Invitational golf event. Spiranac made a name for herself not just in golf, but on social media, where the 32-year-old often posts provocatively on and off the golf course. After posting the heartfelt video, Spiranac is now getting an outpouring of support from her admirers all over social media.
title: Golfer Paige Spiranac Breaks Down After Enduring Cruel Online Trolling

author: Inside Edition
description: One man's half-day excursion in the woods turned into a three-week nightmare that left him fighting for his life. 65-year-old Ron Dailey went on a solo hunting trip in the Sierra National Forest. He says he took a wrong trail and his pickup truck couldn't make it back up the hill, then a storm covered his truck with two feet of snow. Unknown to Dailey, authorities were searching for him. After 20 grueling days, he says he realized he had to hike out. Nine hours later, he ran into three hunters.
title: Man Rescued After Surviving 20 Days Lost in Sierra National Forest

author: Inside Edition
description: A former news anchor is reportedly accused of stabbing her mother to death in Wichita, Kansas. Sheriff's department records say 47-year-old Angelynn Mock is accused of first degree murder and is being held on a million dollars bond. She has yet to make her first court appearance. Mock went by Angie Mock when she was a reporter and anchor for St. Louis' Fox affiliate from 2011 to 2015 according to her LinkedIn profile. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Former News Anchor Accused Of Stabbing Elderly Mother To Death

author: Inside Edition
description: A girl was saved from being swept out of a roller coaster in Missouri when her seatbelt suddenly appeared to come undone and a couple sitting nearby helped hold her inside the ride.
title: Adults Hold On To Girl In Scary Rollercoaster Seatbelt Incident #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: When the baby was born, her parents found out she has the rare condition known as Moebius Syndrome which doesn’t allow her to blink or show facial expressions. The family has set up a GoFundMe to help pay for expenses- https://www.gofundme.com/f/help-tori-and-her-five-special-needs-children-find-a-home
title: Baby Born With Condition That Prevents Her From Blinking #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Thousands of passengers have had to wait for hours to go through security checks, and flights are being delayed across the U.S. as air traffic controllers refrain from working as they don’t get paid amid the government shutdown.
title: Chaos At Airports As Government Shutdown Continues #shorts

description: The legends of Good Morning America are celebrating the show's golden anniversary. The very first anchor was David Hartman, who is now 90 years old.
title: Good Morning America Celebrates Its 50th Anniversary #shorts
